{"schema_version":"1.7.3","id":"OESA-2025-1242","published":"2025-03-07T15:26:53Z","modified":"2025-09-03T06:20:48.915593Z","upstream":["CVE-2025-0395"],"summary":"glibc security update","details":"The GNU C Library project provides the core libraries for the GNU system and GNU/Linux systems, as well as many other systems that use Linux as the kernel. These libraries provide critical APIs including ISO C11, POSIX.1-2008, BSD, OS-specific APIs and more. These APIs include such foundational facilities as open, read, write, malloc, printf, getaddrinfo, dlopen, pthread_create, crypt,  login, exit and more.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nWhen the assert() function in the GNU C Library versions 2.13 to 2.40 fails, it does not allocate enough space for the assertion failure message string and size information, which may lead to a buffer overflow if the message string size aligns to page size.(CVE-2025-0395)","affected":[{"package":{"name":"glibc","ecosystem":"openEuler:24.03-LTS","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/glibc&distro=openEuler-24.03-LTS"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"2.38-54.oe2403sp1"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["glibc-2.38-54.oe2403.aarch64.rpm","glibc-all-langpacks-2.38-54.oe2403.aarch64.rpm","glibc-common-2.38-54.oe2403.aarch64.rpm","glibc-debuginfo-2.38-54.oe2403.aarch64.rpm","glibc-debugsource-2.38-54.oe2403.aarch64.rpm","glibc-debugutils-2.38-54.oe2403.aarch64.rpm","glibc-devel-2.38-54.oe2403.aarch64.rpm","glibc-locale-archive-2.38-54.oe2403.aarch64.rpm","glibc-locale-source-2.38-54.oe2403.aarch64.rpm","glibc-nss-devel-2.38-54.oe2403.aarch64.rpm","libnsl-2.38-54.oe2403.aarch64.rpm","nscd-2.38-54.oe2403.aarch64.rpm","nss_modules-2.38-54.oe2403.aarch64.rpm","glibc-2.38-54.oe2403sp1.aarch64.rpm","glibc-all-langpacks-2.38-54.oe2403sp1.aarch64.rpm","glibc-common-2.38-54.oe2403sp1.aarch64.rpm","glibc-debuginfo-2.38-54.oe2403sp1.aarch64.rpm","glibc-debugsource-2.38-54.oe2403sp1.aarch64.rpm","glibc-debugutils-2.38-54.oe2403sp1.